big and beautiful

00:17.692 --> 00:19.746
♪ Bright lights everywhere

00:19.851 --> 00:22.797
♪ A place where you can meet St Nick

00:22.901 --> 00:25.876
♪ So join our journey there

00:26.012 --> 00:28.267
♪ A Christmas city
is a magical sight

00:28.372 --> 00:31.157
♪ No other place compares

00:31.292 --> 00:33.987
♪ The smell of pine trees
The crackling fires

00:34.082 --> 00:36.027
♪ Christmas is in the air

00:36.132 --> 00:39.187
♪ Gifts for all the reindeers racing

00:39.292 --> 00:41.547
♪ Snowmen come to life

00:41.572 --> 00:44.626
♪ Christmas trees are twice the size

00:44.721 --> 00:47.517
♪ As noel flights arrive

00:47.651 --> 00:50.157
♪ Elves are laughing,
packing presents

00:50.262 --> 00:53.027
♪ To give to one and all

00:53.132 --> 00:55.517
♪ Santa's sleigh is fit to burst

00:55.622 --> 00:58.157
♪ We're gonna have a ball! ♪

00:59.542 --> 01:01.667
It was love at first sight.

01:01.692 --> 01:03.517
Anyone could see that.

01:03.662 --> 01:06.547
And it was obvious that this would
be nothing short

01:06.651 --> 01:08.027
of a whirlwind romance.

01:08.182 --> 01:10.387
Nothing was going
to keep us apart.

01:14.332 --> 01:16.907
Dean Papadopoulos, I love you.

01:17.052 --> 01:19.626
And I think you feel the
same way about me.

01:19.721 --> 01:20.721
Don't you?

01:28.262 --> 01:30.307
I can't believe this
is finally happening.

01:34.391 --> 01:35.725
What are you doing?

01:35.830 --> 01:37.446
Dean.

01:39.591 --> 01:40.591
Is that my hat?

01:43.630 --> 01:45.925
Did you make me into
your snow boyfriend?

01:46.031 --> 01:48.725
No! I was just practicing.

01:52.311 --> 01:53.886
Come on, let's go, you guys.

02:18.847 --> 02:21.053
Katie Lou Decks
told me what happened.

02:24.458 --> 02:26.053
I'm sorry, Sarah.

02:28.328 --> 02:29.513
Dean's a jerk.

02:33.967 --> 02:36.103
Thanks, Nick.

02:36.208 --> 02:37.303
Come on.

02:41.008 --> 02:42.183
Come on!

02:45.048 --> 02:46.103
What are you doing?

02:47.258 --> 02:48.258
Just help me.

03:00.767 --> 03:03.903
Forget about Dean.
You could have any one you want.

03:05.208 --> 03:06.208
He can be short.

03:10.967 --> 03:12.023
Or tall.

03:12.128 --> 03:13.903
If that's what you like.

03:15.048 --> 03:17.183
I like tall. And smart.

03:17.208 --> 03:19.583
Great. Bigger brain.

03:23.458 --> 03:25.822
What else? Somebody brave.

03:25.928 --> 03:27.153
Oh, and romantic.

03:35.897 --> 03:37.942
Someone who can sweep me
off my feet.

03:42.767 --> 03:46.072
And nice. And can make me laugh.

03:54.818 --> 03:56.942
Well, there you go.

03:57.048 --> 03:58.622
Everything you want is right there.

03:58.767 --> 04:01.942
Thanks, Nick.
You're a really good friend.

04:06.818 --> 04:08.973
Let's do this every year,
and one day,

04:08.998 --> 04:11.303
when I finally meet
my dream boyfriend,

04:11.458 --> 04:15.433
we won't have to build him any more.
Now all it needs is a name.

04:15.538 --> 04:16.822
What about Cole?

04:20.048 --> 04:21.742
Yeah, I like Cole.

04:22.847 --> 04:25.184
We'd better take a picture.
You don't want to forget the day

04:25.208 --> 04:26.448
you found a guy of your dreams.

04:32.998 --> 04:35.583
Now all we have to do is
wait. Who knows?

04:35.717 --> 04:37.513
Maybe we won't have to
build it next year.

04:54.887 --> 04:56.223
Ow!

05:00.358 --> 05:01.513
He's so gorgeous.

05:03.847 --> 05:06.942
♪ We wish you a merry Christmas

05:07.998 --> 05:10.742
♪ We wish you a merry Christmas

05:10.847 --> 05:14.153
♪ We wish you a merry Christmas

05:14.248 --> 05:17.663
♪ And a happy New Year

05:22.887 --> 05:24.223
No.

05:29.967 --> 05:31.862
What are you doing?

05:33.288 --> 05:36.433
♪ Now bring us some figgy pudding

05:36.538 --> 05:39.793
♪ Now bring us some figgy pudding

05:40.887 --> 05:43.742
♪ Now bring us some figgy pudding

05:43.847 --> 05:47.183
♪ And a cup of good cheer

05:48.458 --> 05:51.862
♪ We wish you a merry Christmas

05:51.967 --> 05:53.303
Not like that.

05:53.408 --> 05:54.822
♪ And a happy new... ♪

05:54.928 --> 05:56.053
Hi.

06:10.328 --> 06:11.543
Morning, dad. Hey, kid.

06:13.369 --> 06:16.249
This looks great. Yeah, I'm using that
stain you got me for Father's Day.

06:16.300 --> 06:18.451
It's fantastic.
And you shouldn't have done it.

06:18.586 --> 06:20.880
You need to be spending
your money on yourself.

06:20.905 --> 06:22.171
It was practically free.

06:22.266 --> 06:24.601
From Italy. Need any help?

06:24.706 --> 06:26.521
No, Herb and I have it covered.

06:26.626 --> 06:28.241
Herb, can I get a clean rag?

06:32.296 --> 06:33.732
Are you sure you don't want my help?

06:33.756 --> 06:35.351
Well, Herb likes to stay useful.

06:36.546 --> 06:39.351
This table's going to be ready in a
few days. Do you think you can

06:39.546 --> 06:43.271
put it online over the weekend? Of course.
Heading into the office early?

06:43.376 --> 06:45.760
No, um, heading to Nick's.

06:45.865 --> 06:48.561
I thought we'd catch up and...

06:48.706 --> 06:51.760
...have coffee.
I know what that means.

06:51.865 --> 06:53.321
You broke up with Brian.

06:54.655 --> 06:56.960
Yeah. Can't say I'm surprised.

06:57.066 --> 06:59.041
Though you did just start dating.

06:59.146 --> 07:00.271
It's been three weeks.

07:00.426 --> 07:03.271
There's no spark. I figured
I'd let him down gently

07:03.426 --> 07:06.601
before it gets too close to
Christmas and I chicken out.

07:09.756 --> 07:13.960
I don't want to settle for someone just
to have someone to kiss on New Year's Eve.

07:13.985 --> 07:15.630
I don't want you to just
settle either.

07:15.785 --> 07:19.481
But I'm worried that you're
too focused on the spark.

07:19.586 --> 07:21.630
Sometimes love is just a slow burn.

07:21.756 --> 07:22.811
I know.

07:24.266 --> 07:27.271
But I've been waiting my whole life
for someone to sweep me off my feet.

07:27.376 --> 07:28.991
I'm not giving up now.

07:32.196 --> 07:33.601
You and Mom set the bar too high.

07:34.706 --> 07:35.991
I just want what you guys had.

07:43.462 --> 07:45.916
As far as break-ups go, you've
definitely had worse.

07:47.422 --> 07:50.037
Except for the part where the waiter
spilt the soup all over the guy.

07:50.061 --> 07:52.227
Ugh. Yeah, that wasn't great.

07:54.741 --> 07:57.557
Yeah. All right.
I think I've finished.

08:00.102 --> 08:01.357
Sadly, that's pretty accurate.

08:02.811 --> 08:05.477
Yup, another for the Hall of Fame.

08:05.611 --> 08:07.867
You know, you keep burning through
boyfriends like this,

08:08.022 --> 08:10.502
I'm going to have to get another
hard drive to store all those.

08:10.532 --> 08:12.757
If you weren't my best friend,
I'd actually be offended.

08:12.861 --> 08:14.687
I hate to break it to you,

08:14.811 --> 08:18.327
but I'm just way too cool to be your
best friend. Too cool? Yeah, OK!

08:19.611 --> 08:21.397
I always forget how
good you are.

08:21.502 --> 08:22.916
Yeah, you and everyone else.

08:23.061 --> 08:25.437
I take it all isn't well in
the world of cartooning?

08:25.582 --> 08:27.916
Well, I sent out a comic strip
to a few publications.

08:28.022 --> 08:29.117
Got a couple of responses.

08:29.222 --> 08:30.687
Yeah? What did they say?

08:30.811 --> 08:33.116
If I printed them off, I'd have
enough rejection letters

08:33.142 --> 08:34.381
to wallpaper this entire place.

08:39.381 --> 08:40.381
Try this one.

08:44.582 --> 08:45.586
Are you serious?

08:46.741 --> 08:50.861
I showed my boss some of your work and she wants to
meet with you about doing some art for the magazine.

08:51.741 --> 08:53.867
You did this? You did!

08:54.022 --> 08:56.677
You're awesome.
I just made sure she found out.

08:57.991 --> 09:00.557
Maybe we'll get to work
on something together.

09:00.662 --> 09:01.786
Yeah, I'd like that.

09:05.662 --> 09:09.836
I mean, this is good and all, but I
definitely prefer your other work.

09:11.142 --> 09:12.197
Yeah.

09:12.302 --> 09:13.916
You're good, though?

09:15.222 --> 09:16.947
Yeah. It was...

09:17.061 --> 09:18.836
It was my decision, but still.

09:18.941 --> 09:20.677
Break-ups are the worst.

09:22.252 --> 09:24.327
Here's to another Christmas
being single.

09:29.702 --> 09:32.716
You know, I gotta say, you really
ran this one down to the wire.

09:32.811 --> 09:34.277
It's December 12th!

09:34.382 --> 09:35.716
Hello? Wow!

09:35.811 --> 09:36.867
I almost forgot.

09:38.142 --> 09:40.397
Looks like it's another
Christmas building my snow beau.

09:40.502 --> 09:41.757
Yeah.

09:41.861 --> 09:44.327
I should get to work. Right.

09:51.142 --> 09:52.557
Thanks for listening.

09:54.452 --> 09:55.867
You're a great friend, Nick.

09:58.502 --> 09:59.502
See you tonight?

10:04.422 --> 10:05.422
Yeah.

10:09.222 --> 10:10.222
Great friend.

10:19.452 --> 10:20.757
Good morning.

10:27.382 --> 10:28.557
Good morning, Isabel.

10:28.662 --> 10:30.197
Oh, morning, Sarah!

10:30.342 --> 10:32.966
You want some elk jerky?
100% home-made.

10:33.061 --> 10:35.117
Fired up the smoker this weekend.

10:35.222 --> 10:36.997
No, I'm good. Thanks, though.

10:37.142 --> 10:41.477
OK. Let me know if you change your
mind, though, because I got, like...

10:41.502 --> 10:42.836
...like 90lb of it at home.

10:42.941 --> 10:45.637
Wow. Elks are huge.

10:45.782 --> 10:49.836
So, I did it. I ended things with
Brian.

10:49.941 --> 10:51.677
Oh, really? I'm sorry.

10:51.782 --> 10:54.427
You OK? Yeah. It was for the best.

10:54.582 --> 10:56.867
It's not like he was
the one or anything.

10:58.061 --> 10:59.117
I'm not crazy, am I?

10:59.222 --> 11:00.757
For wanting that bolt of lightning?

11:02.092 --> 11:03.786
Well, I've been struck
by lightning before.

11:03.941 --> 11:06.557
Citrus fruit tastes
like pennies now.

11:06.662 --> 11:08.277
Am I giving guys enough of a chance?

11:08.422 --> 11:12.277
Like, does that spark need time to
flare up into a raging fire?

11:12.422 --> 11:15.637
Yeah, I've been caught in
a forest fire, too.

11:15.782 --> 11:17.786
It was like right
after the lightning strike.

11:17.892 --> 11:19.757
That was not a good day.

11:19.892 --> 11:21.966
Like, I want excitement.
I want adventure.

11:22.061 --> 11:23.507
Is that too much to ask?

11:24.811 --> 11:27.677
Well, here. This jerky will take
you on a flavour adventure.

11:30.582 --> 11:32.227
(INTERCOM BUZZER)

11:32.382 --> 11:34.227
Sarah, can I see you in
my office, please?

11:34.342 --> 11:35.966
You know how much I love your work.

11:36.092 --> 11:37.836
You're one of the
best writers we've got.

11:37.972 --> 11:40.637
Frankly, Twin Cities Life wouldn't
be the same without you.

11:40.741 --> 11:41.916
Thank you.

11:42.061 --> 11:44.357
Wait, you're not cheerfully firing
me, are you?

11:44.382 --> 11:45.786
Oh, my gosh, no, no.

11:45.941 --> 11:47.701
I'm so sorry. That's not
what I meant at all.

11:47.741 --> 11:50.507
What I wanted to talk to you about
was the e-mail you sent me,

11:50.662 --> 11:54.066
regarding your request for more
diverse assignments.

11:54.171 --> 11:55.756
The travel section?

11:55.891 --> 11:58.356
Well, I think it would make a great
addition to the magazine.

11:58.501 --> 12:01.066
Give our readers a taste of all
things to explore in the world.

12:01.221 --> 12:04.835
And honestly, I would jump at the
chance to pursue travel writing.

12:04.940 --> 12:06.506
This is Twin Cities Life.

12:06.701 --> 12:11.396
I mean, I think a travel section is just
a teensy bit outside of the magazine's scope.

12:11.531 --> 12:14.866
Oh. And your leisure articles
are so great.

12:15.021 --> 12:16.981
It's like you know the
Twin Cities inside and out.

12:17.091 --> 12:19.556
That's what happens when
you never leave.

12:19.701 --> 12:21.915
Exactly! I mean, who better to write
about

12:22.060 --> 12:24.946
all the amazing things to do
in St Paul and Minneapolis

12:25.091 --> 12:28.146
than somebody who's never been
outside the city limits?

12:28.251 --> 12:29.426
Right.

12:29.531 --> 12:31.116
Uh, I hear you.

12:32.661 --> 12:35.485
I'll stick to what I know.
I knew you'd understand.

12:35.640 --> 12:37.781
You're so great,
Sarah, you know that?

12:39.297 --> 12:40.942
Thanks.

12:53.297 --> 12:55.031
Dad? I'm in here!

12:59.167 --> 13:00.967
Here, let me, let me help
you with that, Herb.

13:09.717 --> 13:11.051
Rough clay?

13:11.157 --> 13:12.572
Yeah, you could say that.

13:12.717 --> 13:17.082
Well, broke up with Brian,
got shut down by my boss,

13:17.107 --> 13:19.332
and later tonight I'll
be building a snowman,

13:19.467 --> 13:21.132
which will serve as a lifelong
reminder

13:21.237 --> 13:22.772
that I've never had anything close

13:22.907 --> 13:24.931
to resembling a romantic,
long-term relationship.

13:25.037 --> 13:26.601
That's one way of looking at it.

13:28.797 --> 13:32.242
Or you dumped your boyfriend because
you weren't right for each other.

13:32.437 --> 13:35.413
From what you tell me on the phone, your
boss is very pleased with your work.

13:35.437 --> 13:37.692
And later tonight you're going to
see your best friend

13:37.826 --> 13:40.801
and partake in a Christmas tradition
that dates back almost 20 years.

13:40.956 --> 13:43.931
You're not supposed to poke holes in
my whining.

13:44.076 --> 13:46.601
It's your fault I'm so wistful,
you know.

13:46.746 --> 13:50.242
Oh, this should be good!
Well, you and Mom met in Paris!

13:50.387 --> 13:52.931
You spent your first year together
travelling Europe.

13:53.076 --> 13:56.082
How am I supposed to be content with
Brian and St Paul, Minnesota?

13:58.157 --> 14:01.082
Dad, do you ever
think about leaving?

14:02.290 --> 14:03.426
Doesn't it make you sad,

14:03.581 --> 14:06.785
staying here?
Sleeping in the same bed?

14:08.251 --> 14:10.035
It's been almost ten years.

14:10.171 --> 14:12.476
You know, there's still
not a day that goes by

14:12.501 --> 14:13.866
that I don't miss your mother.

14:14.021 --> 14:17.346
But leaving behind the
life we built?

14:17.501 --> 14:19.866
It's not going to make me
miss her any less.

14:20.021 --> 14:22.996
When you first saw her,
you knew, didn't you?

14:24.171 --> 14:25.866
All I want is to feel
the same thing.

14:27.341 --> 14:29.955
Do you really think I'm going to
find that if I stay here?

14:30.091 --> 14:32.835
It's not about where
you are, sweetie.

14:32.940 --> 14:34.676
It's about who you're with.

14:35.940 --> 14:37.835
Oh, Dad... l

14:37.980 --> 14:39.785
Come on. I want to
show you something.

14:47.701 --> 14:50.915
I never told you this, but the night
before I met your mother,

14:51.021 --> 14:54.066
I made a wish. You did?

14:55.860 --> 14:57.785
It was Christmas Eve.

14:57.891 --> 14:59.785
I was alone in Paris.

14:59.891 --> 15:01.226
The city of love.

15:02.891 --> 15:05.426
So I wished that I'd
find the love of my life...

15:07.501 --> 15:09.396
...and the next day I saw her.

15:10.860 --> 15:12.915
And she was wearing this.

15:13.060 --> 15:15.396
That's the first thing I noticed
about her,

15:15.581 --> 15:20.585
this bright red scarf in a sea of blacks
and greys in the streets of Paris.

15:21.980 --> 15:24.196
If it hadn't been for this,
I might never have seen her.

15:31.141 --> 15:32.866
You have your mother's heart.

15:33.011 --> 15:36.316
Who knows? Maybe this will work its
magic on you like it did with her.

15:40.341 --> 15:41.866
Thanks, Dad.

15:43.980 --> 15:45.035
(MOBILE VIBRATES)

15:46.421 --> 15:47.835
Oh, it's Nick. He's outside.

15:47.940 --> 15:49.226
See? It's working already.

15:49.341 --> 15:50.866
Dad!

15:50.980 --> 15:53.636
It's Nick. We tried that once.

15:53.781 --> 15:55.346
Didn't work. Oh, sure,
in high school.

15:55.451 --> 15:57.346
But you were kids. And no offense,

15:57.501 --> 15:59.396
but you were both kind
of obnoxious back then.

16:01.730 --> 16:03.556
Go on.

16:03.661 --> 16:04.835
Don't keep him waiting.

16:12.371 --> 16:14.196
Let's go! Hurry up.

16:14.301 --> 16:15.506
It's freezing.

16:18.091 --> 16:19.346
Hey, nice scarf.

16:21.221 --> 16:24.035
Those the goods?
Yup, straight from my closet.

16:24.171 --> 16:26.731
Anything you could possibly need to
build the man of your dreams.

16:26.781 --> 16:28.146
Let's get to work.

16:33.371 --> 16:36.316
OK. He's a blank canvas.

16:36.421 --> 16:38.066
We've got a lot of options.

16:38.171 --> 16:39.506
Hit me.

16:40.980 --> 16:44.346
He's got to be adventurous, not
afraid to go off the beaten path. OK.

16:44.501 --> 16:46.835
Maybe his job lets him travel,
see the world.

16:46.940 --> 16:48.636
Nothing says adventure like flannel.

16:51.531 --> 16:55.066
What's next? This goes without
saying, but he's got to be gorgeous.

16:55.171 --> 16:57.426
Charming. A perfect gentleman.

16:59.940 --> 17:01.317
Are you drawing abs on our snowman?

17:01.341 --> 17:03.316
Don't judge me! OK!

17:03.451 --> 17:05.954
He's got to be smart
but not arrogant, sweet,

17:06.090 --> 17:08.835
down to earth. And he's got to make
me laugh.

17:14.171 --> 17:15.316
Well now he's perfect.

17:17.980 --> 17:20.425
I'd want him to
be incredibly romantic.

17:20.531 --> 17:21.531
Someone who will...

17:21.621 --> 17:24.116
Sweep you off your feet.

17:24.261 --> 17:26.556
I know, you've been saying this
for 20 years!

17:26.651 --> 17:27.675
OK.

17:27.781 --> 17:29.346
Anything else?

17:31.421 --> 17:34.955
I want excitement.
I want my heart to be set on fire.

17:36.810 --> 17:38.626
When I look in his eyes,
I want to know.

17:42.621 --> 17:46.556
Uh, yeah... I don't have
anything for that.

17:57.251 --> 17:58.346
Come on.

18:03.860 --> 18:05.066
Come on.

18:12.141 --> 18:14.316
Hey, smile, come on!

18:22.301 --> 18:25.556
Most of all, I wish this is finally
the year I meet the man of my dreams.

18:27.301 --> 18:30.476
That, come Christmas,
I'll be in love.

18:37.341 --> 18:38.476
You good?

18:40.091 --> 18:41.091
Yeah.

18:42.581 --> 18:43.705
Just tired.

18:45.730 --> 18:47.330
Think I'm going to call
it a night. Yeah.

18:48.730 --> 18:49.835
Text you tomorrow?

18:53.730 --> 18:54.730
Night, Nick.

18:57.171 --> 18:58.266
Goodnight.

19:42.891 --> 19:44.035
Mom.

20:30.681 --> 20:32.176
Hey, morning, kid.

20:32.271 --> 20:33.966
Morning, Dad. This smells good.

20:34.071 --> 20:36.096
You're awfully chipper.

20:36.241 --> 20:38.536
Here I was worried about you
after we talked last night.

20:38.561 --> 20:39.966
I'll admit I was a bit morose,

20:40.121 --> 20:42.816
but it's just a symptom of December
12th that I've dealt with for the

20:42.840 --> 20:45.656
better part of my life. I'm glad
you're feeling better...

20:45.761 --> 20:46.935
It's a zit.

20:47.071 --> 20:48.815
I woke up with it.
But, yeah, I mean,

20:48.960 --> 20:51.406
who cares if I don't fall in
love by Christmas?

20:51.511 --> 20:53.216
I have you, St Paul is fine,

20:53.351 --> 20:56.126
and if I need a change of
scenery I can go to Minneapolis.

20:56.241 --> 20:58.846
Over there, somewhere.

20:58.991 --> 21:02.456
And if I get lonely over the
holidays, I can just get a turtle.

21:02.561 --> 21:04.096
I'll be a turtle lady.

21:04.201 --> 21:05.486
Clearly, you're not fine.

21:05.601 --> 21:07.096
I'm better than fine.

21:07.201 --> 21:08.885
I guess that explains the snowman.

21:08.991 --> 21:10.176
Yeah, it does.

21:10.271 --> 21:12.246
Wait, what are you talking about?

