it is to feel closer to her.

43:36.392 --> 43:40.117
I think he's ready to retire, but I
don't know what I'll do when he does.

43:40.272 --> 43:43.408
The house is technically
mine now, which is great.

43:43.503 --> 43:44.503
Um...

43:46.192 --> 43:49.167
But it just feels
like this big anchor.

43:52.783 --> 43:54.367
Have you ever thought of selling?

43:57.553 --> 43:59.117
I don't know if I could
ever do that.

44:00.553 --> 44:02.278
It's the only home I've ever had.

44:03.863 --> 44:04.917
I understand.

44:06.322 --> 44:09.198
But a ship can't set sail
until it raises anchor.

44:17.272 --> 44:18.912
It's too bad it isn't January.
In a month,

44:18.942 --> 44:21.758
this place is going to be crammed
with people for the winter carnival.

44:21.863 --> 44:23.888
Winter carnival? What's that?

44:24.033 --> 44:27.088
What, you grew up here and you don't
know what the winter carnival is?

44:27.192 --> 44:28.748
No, I'm usually gone by Christmas.

44:28.933 --> 44:34.047
It's this amazing outdoor fair with ice
sculpting and food trucks and music.

44:34.192 --> 44:36.117
It's one of my favourite things
about this city.

44:36.272 --> 44:38.688
Plus, there's like deep-fried
everything.

44:38.783 --> 44:40.247
Like, it's magical.

44:40.392 --> 44:43.398
Do you remember when we were eight
and Katie Wudeckis threw up that

44:43.553 --> 44:45.888
deep-fried Twinkie all over
the ice palace?

44:46.033 --> 44:48.758
I forgot about that. And then Ryan
Schneider slipped and fell in it.

44:48.863 --> 44:50.167
Yeah.

44:50.322 --> 44:54.198
Hey, we've been going to this thing
for, like, 20 years now together.

44:54.353 --> 44:56.917
We have. That's a lot
of good memories.

44:57.033 --> 45:00.558
Yeah. Yeah, a lot of good memories.

45:02.633 --> 45:04.398
So, what's on the agenda?

45:04.553 --> 45:06.558
Only one of the best free activities
available

45:06.713 --> 45:08.728
to everyone in the
Twin Cities during winter.

45:10.473 --> 45:11.808
BOTH: Snow sculpting.

45:13.142 --> 45:14.142
No way. I

45:21.553 --> 45:24.988
I'm so excited right now. Yeah, we're
just basically building snowmen.

45:25.092 --> 45:27.028
Yeah, I love snowmen.

45:27.162 --> 45:29.367
Hey, dibs on that pile right there.
OK?

45:34.072 --> 45:36.247
Oh. OK.

45:36.392 --> 45:39.167
Hey, what do you say we team up and
show Cole how this is done?

45:39.353 --> 45:42.297
This is incredible. Sarah, you've got
to come check this out. Come here!

45:42.423 --> 45:44.448
I'd better go over there
before he hurts himself.

45:44.583 --> 45:46.143
I'm not going to
hurt myself. Come here.

45:47.583 --> 45:48.938
Yeah, that would be terrible.

45:49.993 --> 45:50.993
Real bad.

45:52.493 --> 45:54.267
All right. Here, you take this.

45:54.373 --> 45:55.668
We're going to make a big pile.

45:55.803 --> 45:57.808
Like this big. OK?
OK. Come on. Yeah.

45:57.913 --> 45:59.578
Pile there. Stack it up.

46:01.783 --> 46:03.247
Hey, why don't I be your co-pilot?

46:04.583 --> 46:06.328
No, what's the point?

46:06.473 --> 46:10.047
Well, I mean, you could
beat Cole at something

46:10.192 --> 46:12.528
and rub it in his big,
beautiful face?

46:12.633 --> 46:14.478
You're an artist and...

46:14.583 --> 46:16.608
This is clearly his first time.

46:18.223 --> 46:20.167
What do you say?

46:20.272 --> 46:21.472
Oh, they don't stand a chance.

46:24.223 --> 46:25.398
Oh, yeah.

46:34.312 --> 46:36.198
And you've never done this before?

46:36.312 --> 46:37.758
No. Never. I

46:37.863 --> 46:38.863
I just get snow.

46:42.942 --> 46:44.398
Do you guys see this?

46:45.553 --> 46:46.888
I mean...

46:46.993 --> 46:49.498
I mean, it's good. Yeah.

46:49.603 --> 46:51.838
But, you know, get a load of ours!

46:56.993 --> 46:59.167
Yeah. Yeah.

46:59.192 --> 47:01.758
I like that you've got this
slug thing going on.

47:01.863 --> 47:04.528
No, no. Come on, it's a shark.

47:04.633 --> 47:06.037
Obviously. Like, come on.

47:06.142 --> 47:08.938
See? You get it?

47:09.033 --> 47:11.608
It's got a little Santa hat.

47:11.713 --> 47:15.167
See? Yeah, Santa jaws, right?

47:15.272 --> 47:16.828
Oh! Yeah.

47:16.933 --> 47:19.267
Yeah, no, I see it. It's great.

47:19.443 --> 47:22.399
I've got to be honest, I don't see it,
but hey, I love the effort, little guy.

47:22.423 --> 47:25.558
Come around here,
let's get a picture.

47:25.713 --> 47:29.117
Oh, yeah. Great idea.
We're going to get one...

47:29.223 --> 47:30.917
Come on.

47:32.863 --> 47:35.167
Oh. Ice cream store.

47:35.312 --> 47:37.247
You want ice cream?
It's 15 degrees outside.

47:37.353 --> 47:38.888
I love 15 degrees. I love ice cream.

47:38.993 --> 47:40.528
I love winter.

47:40.633 --> 47:42.008
Yeah? OK. Jump on the sled.

47:42.113 --> 47:43.113
We'll go. I

47:43.142 --> 47:44.367
Shark.

47:51.553 --> 47:54.528
OK, so, if we start
with ice skating,

47:54.673 --> 47:57.928
what about a full page
next to it with this?

47:59.783 --> 48:01.678
That's amazing!

48:01.783 --> 48:03.968
I love how you captured the moment.

48:04.062 --> 48:05.838
That's really wonderful.

48:05.953 --> 48:07.608
Yeah, we have to use that.

48:07.703 --> 48:09.728
Yeah. Thanks.

48:09.863 --> 48:13.218
We should also think about
a picture for the front page.

48:13.412 --> 48:16.248
She hasn't asked yet, but knowing
Amanda, she's going to want, you know,

48:16.272 --> 48:19.608
this perfect image that
encapsulates the future story.

48:19.703 --> 48:21.678
Yeah. Any ideas?

48:21.833 --> 48:25.367
I... I can mock up a
few drawings here.

48:25.503 --> 48:29.037
It would have to be something
meaningful, something important.

48:29.142 --> 48:30.328
Yeah.

48:32.863 --> 48:34.808
Hey, what about, um...

48:37.473 --> 48:40.398
What about something
like this? Cole?

48:40.503 --> 48:42.928
Hi. Hi, what are you doing here?

48:43.062 --> 48:44.502
I'm sorry. I don't want to
interrupt.

48:44.633 --> 48:46.928
I just thought that maybe you could
use some brain fuel.

48:46.953 --> 48:48.608
That's so thoughtful.

48:48.753 --> 48:51.917
Thank you. I hope you like
traditional Nordic cuisine.

48:53.223 --> 48:55.287
I found this great
Norwegian restaurant.

48:57.312 --> 49:00.416
And, apparently, they have the best
lutefisk in town.

49:01.601 --> 49:04.526
Lutefisk? Yeah.
It's what people eat.

49:04.671 --> 49:06.896
I mean, the locals, you know.
It's fish.

49:08.441 --> 49:09.616
Oh, yeah. I

49:10.801 --> 49:13.005
Yeah, no, I'm pretty
sure that's pudding.

49:13.160 --> 49:17.005
Ha! You're funny! I've got
another fork. There you go.

49:17.110 --> 49:19.446
Ladies first. Here you are.

49:19.601 --> 49:21.616
And don't think I forgot
about you, little guy.

49:21.721 --> 49:22.896
Oh, great. Yeah.

49:23.030 --> 49:27.296
That's... Eat up.
Yeah, eat up, Sarah.

49:28.601 --> 49:29.601
Yeah. OK.

49:29.721 --> 49:33.255
Yeah. You know what? I like trying
new things so this is...

49:37.751 --> 49:39.286
Mm!

49:39.391 --> 49:41.056
I knew she'd like it.

49:41.160 --> 49:43.135
(SHE COUGHS)

49:43.240 --> 49:44.286
You OK? I

49:44.441 --> 49:47.056
I'm just not really used
to the consistency.

49:47.191 --> 49:49.056
I'm sorry. I totally should have
asked you

49:49.191 --> 49:51.526
what your favourite
take-out was. BOTH: Burritos.

49:53.641 --> 49:56.696
Sorry. I think the lutefisk is about
to swim to the surface.

49:56.801 --> 49:59.335
Swim? What? No, Sarah?

50:01.030 --> 50:03.166
What? What happened? What did I do?

50:09.721 --> 50:11.166
Hey, is she OK?

50:11.311 --> 50:15.646
Well, she's in bed with a bucket
beside her, so she's been better,

50:15.671 --> 50:17.416
but nothing to worry about.

50:17.521 --> 50:19.215
It's Katie Wudeckis all over again.

50:19.311 --> 50:20.576
(LAUGHTER)

50:20.671 --> 50:22.646
It's my fault. Relax, dude.

50:22.801 --> 50:25.085
She ate some bad fish.
It's not the end of the world.

50:25.110 --> 50:26.646
I want to make her feel better.

50:26.801 --> 50:29.536
I don't want her to Katie
Wudeckis into a bucket.

50:29.671 --> 50:32.696
OK, well, I'm going to leave you
guys to it.

50:32.831 --> 50:34.311
I'm going to go back and
check on her.

50:36.360 --> 50:38.056
Thanks, Alan. Yeah, thank you, sir.

50:44.471 --> 50:45.976
Can I ask you a serious question?

50:47.441 --> 50:49.286
Yeah. What brought you here?

50:50.801 --> 50:52.726
See, Sarah thinks it's

50:52.881 --> 50:55.696
fate or a Christmas miracle or
something, I don't know.

50:55.831 --> 51:00.646
I just, I don't buy it.
You don't believe in fate?

51:00.751 --> 51:01.936
Only when it feels right.

51:03.441 --> 51:04.896
Did you plan all this?

51:06.471 --> 51:09.416
Did you look her up online, learn some
things about her to win her over?

51:10.671 --> 51:12.366
I just showed up.

51:13.921 --> 51:15.496
Look, Nick, I know what
this is about.

51:15.601 --> 51:16.856
Your Sarah's best friend.

51:18.110 --> 51:20.750
You want to make sure that she ends
up with a good guy. I get that.

51:23.881 --> 51:25.005
I promise you...

51:26.601 --> 51:29.255
...making sure that Sarah's happy is
the only thing I care about.

51:30.831 --> 51:33.496
You know that she made a wish to
fall in love by Christmas?

51:34.921 --> 51:36.041
How did you know about that?

51:37.240 --> 51:38.776
She told me.

51:38.921 --> 51:42.005
I don't want there to be any
bad blood between us, OK?

51:42.110 --> 51:44.446
So if you need to ask me anything,

51:44.601 --> 51:47.856
to make sure that my intentions
are true with Sarah, ask.

51:49.831 --> 51:51.005
OK, little guy?

51:55.160 --> 51:56.926
OK, so where did you go to college?

51:57.081 --> 52:00.856
I didn't. I've been travelling for
as long as I can remember.

52:00.951 --> 52:02.151
Yeah, I got a better education

52:02.240 --> 52:04.286
living in igloos than I would have
in the classroom.

52:06.160 --> 52:07.335
Yeah, OK, that's great,

52:07.471 --> 52:11.286
but what's the name of the adventure
tourism company that you work for?

52:11.391 --> 52:13.646
Adventure Tourism Company.

52:13.831 --> 52:18.286
I don't know. I mean, it's kind of
weird not having a permanent address, right?

52:18.471 --> 52:21.696
I never stay put long enough to have
one. I don't see what the big deal is.

52:24.160 --> 52:26.416
So, you don't know where they are?

52:27.561 --> 52:29.135
No, never really met my parents.

52:30.441 --> 52:33.176
Oh. That must have been really hard.

52:36.160 --> 52:38.255
How are you doing over there, little
guy?

52:38.441 --> 52:42.856
So, what about this year? Are you planning
on sticking around for Christmas?

52:44.360 --> 52:48.536
You know what, I mean, I have some deadlines
at work, but just depends where I'm at with those.

52:48.561 --> 52:50.726
Are you warm? Ls it warm out here?

52:50.831 --> 52:52.446
Finding it really warm.

52:52.561 --> 52:53.976
I've got to cool down.

53:02.671 --> 53:03.696
Wow.

53:18.201 --> 53:19.646
OK.

53:19.751 --> 53:21.926
It's done. Like, all of it?

53:23.240 --> 53:24.240
Take a look.

53:27.360 --> 53:29.806
I'm still tinkering with the title,
but other than that,

53:29.921 --> 53:31.806
it's ready to send to Amanda.

53:35.280 --> 53:37.416
Do you hate it?

53:37.441 --> 53:39.926
No. No, no, I like it.

53:41.311 --> 53:43.085
It's very accurate.

53:43.191 --> 53:44.416
Yeah?

53:45.671 --> 53:46.896
That means a lot to me.

53:51.521 --> 53:52.776
(MOBILE VIBRATES)

53:55.030 --> 53:56.926
It's... Cole.

53:57.081 --> 53:59.536
He is asking when I'll be
back at the house.

54:01.160 --> 54:02.255
He has a surprise for me.

54:06.441 --> 54:09.005
Come on, then. Better get you back.

54:12.941 --> 54:14.036
Hey.

54:15.610 --> 54:16.916
Hey-HEY-

54:17.011 --> 54:18.011
Hi.

54:19.331 --> 54:21.396
Are you ready for
your surprise? Yeah.

54:26.730 --> 54:28.786
Dean Papadopoulos?

54:28.891 --> 54:29.891
Hey, Sarah.

54:31.251 --> 54:32.316
Wait, is this your house?

54:32.421 --> 54:33.421
What are you doing here?

54:35.061 --> 54:36.061
I asked him to come.

54:36.141 --> 54:38.585
You were right, Cole.
This place is sick.

54:38.701 --> 54:40.316
That's a real estate term.

54:41.701 --> 54:43.276
What is he talking about?

54:43.421 --> 54:45.705
You know what? I think you will be
pleasantly surprised.

54:45.730 --> 54:47.676
You listed the house?

54:47.860 --> 54:51.316
No, of course not. I informally pitched
the idea around town, that's all.

54:51.421 --> 54:53.196
Why? That is none of your business.

54:53.331 --> 54:55.131
I know, I just thought it would be a
good idea

54:55.301 --> 54:58.476
to talk through all the options. Talk?
You want to talk to Dean Papadopoulos?

54:58.610 --> 55:01.196
Nothing is officially
listed. Nothing is happening. Sarah?

55:03.221 --> 55:05.346
I did this for you.
How is this for me?

55:05.371 --> 55:07.226
You said this place was an anchor.

55:07.371 --> 55:09.171
OK, perhaps it's too big for you and
your dad.

55:09.221 --> 55:11.426
OK, you also said that your dad
wanted to retire, right?

55:11.610 --> 55:16.316
(DISTANT): So what! That doesn't give you the
right to intervene. Cole, we just started dating.

55:16.421 --> 55:18.146
Is this their first fight?

55:18.301 --> 55:22.226
Yeah. I guess Sarah's
dream man's human after all.

55:22.341 --> 55:25.226
Try not to act so cavalier.

55:25.341 --> 55:27.036
My daughter's upset.

55:27.141 --> 55:28.705
Yes, sir. Sorry, sir.

55:30.780 --> 55:32.146
Nick... l

55:33.451 --> 55:37.585
You know I have always rooted for
